HEADWORD: Tank vessel
<hw>Tank vessel</hw> }</mhw>.
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A vessel fitted with tanks for the carrying of
oil or other liquid in bulk; -- called also <altname>tanker</altname>. A
tank ship of very large capacity is called a
<stype>supertanker</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

